  the  number  of  child  labour  is  highest  in our country  children are compelled to work in farms factories etc due to weaker economic condition of their families  they have no option but to work to earn a living for them  as per a report of the last year about 5000 children disappeared in assam alone  where do these children go  nobody knows about this  these are  the  issues  which  need  to  be  considered  seriously  because  we  cannot  find  a solution to this problem by amending laws alone  today the need of the hour is to provide education to such children  we are providing education to  such children through  the  ajmal  foundation  in  our  state  and  we  have  achieved  cent  percent success  on  this  count    all  the  members  of  parliament  could    also  prevent  child labour in their areas by making arrangements for education of these children    